==English==

===Etymology===
Latin [[crassus]] 'dense'
#: Example: [[Ulmus crassifolia]] is the Small Leaf Elm, a hardwood tree common to the southern U.S.A., whose small leaves often grow close together on numerous small twigs, hence the species name [[crass]] 'dense' [[folia]] 'foliage'.

===Adjective===
'''crass'''
#Coarse; crude; not or refined or sensible.
#Materialistic


